Package com.amazonaws.mobile.auth.core.signin

Interface SignInProvider

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IdentityProvider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CognitoUserPoolsSignInProvider, FacebookSignInProvider, GoogleSignInProvider
    public interface SignInProvider
extends IdentityProvider
    Each sign-in provider implements this interface, in order to do sign-in button initialization and to handle activity results that have been passed back to the app, after a sign-in provider window has been dismissed.

      • isRequestCodeOurs

        boolean isRequestCodeOurs​(int requestCode)
        Call isRequestCodeOurs to determine if this provider should handle an activity result.
        Parameters:
        requestCode - the requestCode from a previous call to onActivityResult.
        Returns:
        true if the request code is from this provider, otherwise false.

      • initializeSignInButton

        android.view.View.OnClickListener initializeSignInButton​(android.app.Activity signInActivity,
                                                         android.view.View buttonView,
                                                         SignInProviderResultHandler resultsHandler)
        Initialize the sign-in button for the sign-in activity.
        Parameters:
        signInActivity - the activity for sign-in.
        buttonView - the view for the sign-in button to initialize.
        resultsHandler - the resultsHandler for provider sign-in.
        Returns:
        the onClickListener for the button to be able to override the listener, and null if the button cannot be initialized.
